    aboutTreatment:
      "During IV therapy at Hello Gorgeous, a provider reviews your history, checks vital signs as appropriate, and selects a formulation aligned with your goals and safety. Sessions typically run 30 to 60 minutes in a comfortable setting. We offer options focused on hydration, energy support, immune-support nutrients where appropriate, and beauty-forward blends with ingredients chosen for tolerability—not miracle claims. Clients from Naperville, Aurora, and Plainfield often pair IV visits with Botox in Oswego or Hormone Therapy in Oswego for a comprehensive wellness day. We do not promise cures; we focus on education, screening, and appropriate use. Serving the Fox Valley, we bring IV therapy closer to home than hospital-adjacent clinics downtown. Catheter placement uses aseptic technique; bags and additives are prepared with attention to compatibility and osmolarity. If you are new to IV therapy, we explain each ingredient in plain language and how it differs from oral supplements.",
    candidacy:
      "Good candidates are generally healthy adults seeking hydration or nutrient support with realistic expectations. We may defer treatment if you have certain heart or kidney conditions, are pregnant without clearance, or show signs of acute illness that needs urgent care. Medications and allergies are reviewed before infusion. Aurora, IL and Fox Valley residents trust our screening process. If IV therapy is not right today, we guide you to safer alternatives. We also support clients in PRF Hair Restoration in Oswego and RF microneedling who want adjunctive hydration. Your safety determines every decision we make. Athletes with dehydration, professionals recovering from long travel, and clients tapering illness-related fluid losses may benefit when cleared—but we still individualize every bag rather than using a one-size-fits-all menu.",
